<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-2992] Cassandra doesn&apos;t start on Red Hat Linux due to hardcoded JAVA_HOME</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-2992</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;On CentOS /etc/init.d/cassandra has&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;export JAVA_HOME=/usr/lib/jvm/java-1.6.0-openjdk-1.6.0.0/&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;While there is no such a directory on our server it was ok for 0.8.2, because /usr/sbin/cassandra checked the executable&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;if [ -x $JAVA_HOME/bin/java ]; then&lt;br/&gt;
    JAVA=$JAVA_HOME/bin/java&lt;br/&gt;
else&lt;br/&gt;
    JAVA=`which java`&lt;br/&gt;
fi&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;But 0.8.3 builds replaced the above code with one that doesn&apos;t check if JAVA_HOME is set correctly.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;if [ -n &quot;$JAVA_HOME&quot; ]; then&lt;br/&gt;
    JAVA=&quot;$JAVA_HOME/bin/java&quot;&lt;br/&gt;
else&lt;br/&gt;
    JAVA=java&lt;br/&gt;
fi&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;That&apos;s why cassandra doesn&apos;t start anymore.&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;The correct fix would be to remove &quot;export JAVA_HOME&quot; from /etc/init.d/cassandra or set it only to correct path and only if it hasn&apos;t already been set.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It would also be nice to revert to &quot;[ -x $JAVA_HOME/bin/java ]&quot; in /usr/sbin/cassandra&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;CentOS release 5.6&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
